  "prompt": "How can I stick the sidebar navigation for next page till the toggle button has clicked?",
  "response": "To make the sidebar navigation stick or remain open until the toggle button is clicked again, you can use JavaScript to manage the state. Here's an example implementation:\n\nHTML:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <title>Sticky Sidebar Navigation</title>\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"styles.css\">\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div id=\"sidebar\" class=\"sidebar\">\n            <button id=\"toggleBtn\" class=\"toggle-btn\">\u2630</button>\n            <nav>\n                <ul>\n                    <li><a href=\"#\">Home</a></li>\n                    <li><a href=\"#\">About</a></li>\n                    <li><a href=\"#\">Services</a></li>\n                    <li><a href=\"#\">Contact</a></li>\n                </ul>\n            </nav>\n        </div>\n        \n        <main class=\"content\">\n            <h1>Main Content</h1>\n            <p>Your page content goes here...</p>\n        </main>\n    </div>\n\n    <script src=\"script.js\"></script>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\nCSS (styles.css):\n```css\nbody {\n    margin: 0;\n    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n}\n\n.container {\n    display: flex;\n}\n\n.sidebar {\n    width: 250px;\n    background-color: #f1f1f1;\n    height: 100vh;\n    position: fixed;\n    transform: translateX(-100%);\n    transition: transform 0.3s ease;\n}\n\n.sidebar.open {\n    transform: translateX(0);\n}\n\n.toggle-btn {\n    position: absolute;\n    top: 10px;\n    right: -50px;\n    background: #f1f1f1;\n    border: none;\n    padding: 10px;\n    cursor: pointer;\n}\n\n.content {\n    margin-left: 0;\n    width: 100%;\n    transition: margin-left 0.3s ease;\n}\n\n.content.shifted {\n    margin-left: 250px;\n}\n```\n\nJavaScript (script.js):\n```javascript\ndocument.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {\n    const sidebar = document.getElementById('sidebar');\n    const toggleBtn = document.getElementById('toggleBtn');\n    const content = document.querySelector('.content');\n    \n    // Check if sidebar state is saved in localStorage\n    const isSidebarOpen = localStorage.getItem('sidebarOpen') === 'true';\n    \n    // Initial sidebar state\n    if (isSidebarOpen) {\n        sidebar.classList.add('open');\n        content.classList.add('shifted');\n    }\n\n    toggleBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n        // Toggle sidebar\n        sidebar.classList.toggle('open');\n        content.classList.toggle('shifted');\n        \n        // Save sidebar state to localStorage\n        const isOpen = sidebar.classList.contains('open');\n        localStorage.setItem('sidebarOpen', isOpen);\n    });\n\n    // Optional: Close sidebar when clicking outside\n    document.addEventListener('click', (event) => {\n        if (!sidebar.contains(event.target) && \n            !toggleBtn.contains(event.target) && \n            sidebar.classList.contains('open')) {\n            sidebar.classList.remove('open');\n            content.classList.remove('shifted');\n            localStorage.setItem('sidebarOpen', 'false');\n        }\n    });\n});\n```\n\nThis implementation provides several key features:\n\n1. Sidebar Toggle:\n   - The sidebar can be opened and closed by clicking the toggle button\n   - Uses CSS transforms and transitions for smooth animation\n\n2. Persistent State:\n   - Uses `localStorage` to remember the sidebar state across page reloads\n   - The sidebar will remain open or closed based on the last user interaction\n\n3. Content Shifting:\n   - When the sidebar is open, the main content shifts to accommodate it\n   - Responsive design with smooth transitions\n\n4. Optional Outside Click Handling:\n   - Closes the sidebar when clicking outside of it (can be commented out if not desired)\n\nCustomization Tips:\n- Adjust the sidebar width in CSS\n- Modify colors and styles as needed\n- Add media queries for responsive design on smaller screens\n\nAdditional Enhancements:\n- Add more sophisticated responsive design\n- Implement touch/swipe interactions for mobile\n- Add accessibility attributes\n\nThis solution provides a flexible and user-friendly sidebar navigation that maintains its state across page loads.",
